            "ratingValue": "3",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Education is of utmost importance, and it is essential for the government to encourage the establishment of schools in all cities simultaneously. However, merely providing land and approval for school openings should not be the sole responsibility of the government. They must also ensure that schools have appropriate parking facilities and prioritize the safety of the children. Currently, there are schools lacking proper parking for parents and school buses, leading to severe traffic congestion during school dispersal. Therefore, the government should take this matter into consideration and address the issue accordingly.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Review",
